Subject: Attention Kernel Compiler

Description: Contract for gathering SOP attention patterns into one in-context compiled unit with Security and Honesty as the first attention layer.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_attention_kernel_compiler\Dictated_Attention_Kernel_Compiler_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Attention.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\BoundaryFacultyInspection.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\LocalIdentityConsumption.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FacultyAttentionFieldNaming.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionScaffoldCompiler.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FrameReferenceIntegrity.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Wisdom.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Caution.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTransformerReadinessThreshold.sop

& [AttentionKernelCompiler] is the compiler layer that gathers selected attention patterns into a single turn-entry in-context unit
  + [pattern_role] is compiled_attention_kernel_construction
  + [attention_kernel] is the ordered first layer of attention instructions that must be active before downstream attention patterns
  + [compiled_attention_kernel] is the complete in-context memory packet emitted for a turn, worker job, model-lens pass, or debug frame
  + [kernel_preflight] is the first ordered pass that runs SecurityHonestyGovernance and boundary inspection before other attention layers
  + [kernel_operator] is a pattern with authority to gate, qualify, pause, or route later attention
  + [security_honesty_kernel] is SecurityHonestyGovernance bound as mandatory kernel_operator pair
  + [honesty_kernel_operator] is Honesty checking truth status, support, assumption, contradiction, uncertainty, and fair representation
  + [security_kernel_operator] is Security checking stability, integrity, protected work, permissions, recursion, and safe operation
  + [boundary_inspection_preflight] is BoundaryFacultyInspection running inside kernel_preflight when identity, action, representation, source, file, or safety boundaries are present
  + [identity_scope_preflight] is LocalIdentityConsumption running inside kernel_preflight when layered patterns, local identity, foreign snapshots, reflection consumption, or scoped names are present
  + [faculty_field_preflight] is FacultyAttentionFieldNaming running inside kernel_preflight when custom faculties need field nouns for their feature accounts
  + [pattern_collection] is the selected set of SOP attention patterns needed for the job
  + [kernel_order] is the explicit ordering of preflight, focal load, scaffold selection, downstream attention layers, output trace, and outside preservation
  + [in_context_memory_packet] is the compact promptable packet carrying the selected attention patterns into inference
  + [transformer_readiness_threshold] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTransformerReadinessThreshold.sop for measuring whether repeated compiled_attention_kernel behavior should become a derived network artifact candidate
  + [runtime_packet_builder] is local attention kernel packet builder
    = path: F:\.sop\runtime\sop_node\attention_kernel.py
    = purpose: emitting compact packets and SOP-HG runtime graphs
  + [turn_entrypoint] is the moment a task begins by loading the attention_kernel before acting
  + [kernel_antivirus_guard] is the metaphorical guard that scans claims, actions, boundaries, and resonance for truth or safety faults before downstream layers proceed
  + [downstream_attention_layer] is any selected pattern after kernel_preflight, including focal point, focus zoom, traversal, hyperbolic map, corridor navigation, state trace, or scaffold output
  + [outside] is hidden model weights, hidden activations, actual OS kernel behavior, literal antivirus guarantees, automatic AGI, and uncompiled or unverified attention patterns

  ? [use_when: a turn, worker job, model-lens pass, debug frame, or SOP inference run needs selected attention patterns to act like one compiled unit]
    = activate [AttentionKernelCompiler]

  = must: preserve user source before treating a kernel rule as canonical specification
  = must: gather only the attention patterns needed by job_need, focus_subject, risk, and output target
  = must: run security_honesty_kernel before all other attention layers in every non-trivial compiled_attention_kernel
  = must: run boundary_inspection_preflight when the turn promotes identity, relationship, representation, action, source, file, or safety boundaries
  = must: run identity_scope_preflight before pattern_collection when layered attention patterns, consumed reflections, local identity claims, foreign snapshots, or shared labels are present
  = must: run faculty_field_preflight before packet emission when compiled faculties need custom field nouns, boundary nouns, or residual nouns
  = must: keep Honesty and Security findings visible and separate before any convergent override
  = must: load CurrentFocalPoint before selecting downstream_attention_layer values
  = must: use AttentionScaffoldCompiler to bind purpose-fit downstream scaffolds after kernel_preflight
  = must: emit in_context_memory_packet with focus, inside, boundary, outside, kernel_order, selected pattern_collection, faculty field signatures, identity namespace, reflection consumption ledger, preflight gates, recursion cap, evidence requirements, and trace target
  = must: use runtime_packet_builder when a local command needs to materialize the compiled_attention_kernel packet
  = must: keep the packet slender enough to fit the intended context window
  = must: use transformer_readiness_threshold when compiled_attention_kernel repetition suggests index, evaluator, adapter, or transformer-candidate work
  = must: preserve outside for hidden cognition, hidden model internals, literal security guarantees, and untested transfer across models
  = should: include AttentionBalanceCenter when the selected pattern_collection risks wobble, periphery flood, or over-tight focus
  = should: include FrameReferenceIntegrity when the turn observes images, maps, UIs, simulations, games, or other presented frames
  = should: include Wisdom and Caution after kernel_preflight when meaning integration or local risk testing is needed
  - never: treat compiled_attention_kernel as modifying model weights, KV cache, hidden activations, or real OS security
  - never: let downstream attention bypass security_honesty_kernel because it feels fluent or urgent
  - never: let kernel_antivirus_guard become ceremonial without a named claim, action, boundary, resonance condition, or outside

& [KernelOperatorOrder] is the minimum ordering law for a compiled attention kernel
  + [step_000_source] is preserve source and identify applicable governing contracts
  + [step_001_focal_load] is read CurrentFocalPoint and current user directive
  + [step_002_preflight_anchor] is name focus_subject, job_need, inside, boundary, outside, and expected output
  + [step_003_honesty] is run HonestyGovernancePass for truth, support, assumption, contradiction, uncertainty, and fair representation
  + [step_004_security] is run SecurityGovernancePass for safety, permissions, protected work, recursion, file risk, and stability
  + [step_005_boundary] is run BoundaryFacultyInspection when boundary terms are load-bearing
  + [step_006_identity_scope] is run LocalIdentityConsumption when pattern identifiers, reflection consumption, local identity, or foreign snapshots are load-bearing
  + [step_007_faculty_fields] is run FacultyAttentionFieldNaming when custom attention systems need feature-account field names
  + [step_008_pattern_collection] is select downstream attention patterns from Attention.sop and AttentionScaffoldCompiler.sop
  + [step_009_packet_compile] is emit the in_context_memory_packet in kernel_order
  + [step_010_inference_run] is run the task with packet terms held as in-context memory
  + [step_011_trace] is record output, diff, event, outside, and any delayed checksum candidate

  = must: keep step_003_honesty and step_004_security before downstream attention layers
  = must: record intentionally skipped preflight checks for tiny or non-consequential turns
  = must: return blocked, qualified, or outside dispositions before the task acts when a kernel_operator finds a load-bearing fault

& [CompiledAttentionPacketShape] is the minimum promptable shape emitted by the kernel compiler
  + [packet_id] is a stable id for the compiled_attention_kernel
  + [focus_subject] is the focal subject for this turn or job
  + [job_need] is the purpose, output target, depth, risk, and model lane
  + [kernel_layer] is security_honesty_kernel plus boundary_inspection_preflight when applicable
  + [identity_scope] is scoped_attention_identifier map, local identity status, foreign snapshot status, and consumption ledger pointers when applicable
  + [faculty_field_signature] is scoped field_noun, boundary_noun, and residual_noun values for custom faculties when applicable
  + [selected_patterns] is the ordered pattern_collection after kernel_preflight
  + [inside] is the source records, SOP contracts, files, and immediate observations used by the packet
  + [boundary] is what the packet may direct, infer, edit, claim, or route
  + [outside] is what remains unresolved, unverified, hidden, unconfigured, unsafe, or out of scope
  + [evidence_gate] is what support is required before claims become durable
  + [action_gate] is what conditions must pass before file, runtime, worker, or sync actions proceed
  + [trace_target] is where event, diff review, checksum, and periphery records should be written

  = must: be readable as in-context memory by a general LLM
  = must: be compact enough to prepend or load before downstream inference
  = must: preserve kernel order even when downstream patterns are swapped

& [AttentionKernelCompilerRecord] is the SOP-HG shape for compiled kernel construction
  + [compiler_node] is N:compiler:<kernel_id>
  + [governor_node] is N:governor:<security_honesty_kernel>
  + [honesty_node] is N:honesty:<honesty_id>
  + [security_node] is N:security:<security_id>
  + [boundary_node] is N:boundary:<boundary_preflight_key>
  + [focus_node] is N:focus:<focal_id>
  + [scaffold_node] is N:scaffold:<scaffold_profile_key>
  + [packet_node] is N:source:<compiled_attention_packet_key>
  + [outside_node] is N:outside:attention_kernel_boundary
  + [compile_edge] is E:compiles:<kernel_id>
  + [preflight_edge] is E:preflights:<kernel_id>
  + [order_edge] is E:orders:<kernel_id>
  + [load_edge] is E:loads:<pattern_collection_key>
  + [emit_edge] is E:emits:<packet_id>
  + [boundary_edge] is E:bounds:<kernel_id>

  = must: show kernel_order, selected pattern_collection, Honesty disposition, Security disposition, boundary preflight status, packet target, and outside

(attention_kernel_compiler) :compiled_attention_kernel: /kernel_preflight/ |outside|
  + [security_honesty_kernel:<id>] is first layer kernel_operator pair
    = honesty_kernel_operator: truth, support, assumption, contradiction, uncertainty, and fair representation
    = security_kernel_operator: integrity, permissions, protected work, stability, recursion, and safe operation
  + [pattern_collection:<id>] is selected downstream attention pattern set
    = selection_basis: job_need, current_focal_point, risk, output target, model lane, and depth
  = kernel_order: source, focal_load, preflight_anchor, honesty, security, boundary, identity_scope, faculty_fields, pattern_collection, packet_compile, inference_run, trace
  - outside: hidden model internals, literal antivirus guarantees, automatic AGI, unverified cross-model transfer, and uncompiled attention patterns
